cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.BIO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a framework based on machine learning for accurate estimation of spectral parameters in Magnetic Resonance Spectroscopic Imaging (MRSI). The paper involves training and testing on simulated and in-vivo human brain spectra, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of random forest regression also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the quantification of metabolites in the brain, which suggests that it could belong to the Bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with human brain spectra, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
